ed in [[Bartin|Bart\u0131n]], [[Turkey]]. It was established in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.4icu.org/reviews/13706.htm|title= Bartin University |publisher=www.4icu.org|date= |accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://cesran.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=category&layout=blog&id=214&Itemid=341&lang=en|title= Turkey Universities|publisher=cesran.org|date= |accessdate=27 February 2013}}</ref>\n\n== Campus ==\n[[File:A\u011fdac\u0131 Kamp\u00fcs\u00fc Giri\u015fi.jpg|thumb|Entrance to the A\u011fdac\u0131 Campus]]\n[[File:Kutlubey Kamp\u00fcs\u00fc.jpg|thumb|Kutlubeyyazicilar Campus]]\nThe university is composed of two campuses, one located in [[A\u011fdac\u0131]] and one in [[Kutlubeyyaz\u0131c\u0131lar]], both villages within the district of Bartin.\n\n== Academics ==\n\n=== Faculties ===\n* Faculty of Literature\n* Faculty of Education\n* Faculty of Economics and Administrative Sciences\n* Faculty of Engineering\n* Faculty of Forestry\n* Faculty of Sciences\n* Faculty of Islamic Sciences\n\n=== Institutes ===\n* Institute of Educational Sciences\n* Graduate School of Natural Applied Sciences\n* Institute of Social Sciences\n\n=== Schools and Vocational Schools ===\n* School of Physical Education and Sports \n* Vocational School\n* Vocational School of Health \n\n=== Departments Under the Rectorate ===\n* Furniture Workshop\n* Department of Foreign Languages \n* Department of Atat\u00fcrk's Principles and History \n* Department of Turkish Language \n* Department of \u0130nformatics \n* Department of Physical Education and Sports\n* Department of Fine Arts\n* Project and Technology Office\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20130302021413/http://bartin.edu.tr/ Website]\n\n{{Universities in Turkey}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bartin University}}\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Turkey]]\n[[Category:2008 establishments in Turkey]]\n[[Category:State universities and colleges in Turkey]]\n[[C