{"title_page": "Baresan University", "text_new": "{{more citations needed|date=April 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n| name = Baresan University\n| caption = \u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629 \u0628\u0631\u064a\u0633\u0646\n| motto = Education is a powerful Weapon to change the World.\n| established = 2010\n| type = [[Private university|Private]]\n| rector = Dr. [[Abdi Abdullahi Mohamed]]\n| president = Dr [[Abdulrazak Adam Jimale]]\n| students = 2,625\n| undergrad = 2,195\n| postgrad = 430\n| city = [[Mogadishu]]\n| state = [[Banaadir]]\n| country = [[Somalia]]\n| campus = [[Mogadishu|Mogadishu Campus]], [[Lower Shabelle|Lower Shabelle Compus]]\n| nickname = BSU\n| website = {{url|http://baresanuniversity.net/}}\n| logo = \n| image_name = \n| colors = Orange and Navy<br />{{color box|#f29320}}&nbsp;{{color box|#303083}}\n}}\n\n'''Baresan University''' ('''BSU''') ([[Arabic language|Arabic]]: \u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629 \u0628\u0631\u064a\u0633\u0646, [[Somali language|Somali]]: ''Jaamacada Bare san'') is a [[Private university|private]] [[higher education]] [[institution]] which is [[non-political]], [[Nonpartisanism|non-partisan]] and [[Nonsectarian|non-sectarian]]. It was established in 2010. Baresan University was established at a time when young Somali [[Secondary school|secondary]] graduates could hardly get an opportunity to continue their [[education]] after [[secondary school]] due to the scarcity of tertiary [[education]] [[institution]]s in [[Somalia]].\n\n== History ==\nThe collapse of the [[Somalia|Somali state]] and the subsequent [[Somali Civil War|civil war]](s) from 1990s have altered most aspects of [[Somali people|Somali]] lives ; but they have been particularly devastating in the area of [[education]], where an entire [[generation]] has lost out on one of the most precious opportunities of [[childhood]] and adults. The restoration of regular schooling and [[Somalia universities|universities]] are critical if [[Somali people|Somalis]] expect to survive the present upheaval and envision a hopeful [[future]].\n\nThe scheme to launch Baresan University was advanced by a group of intellectuals led by Dr [[Abdulrazak Adam Jimale]]. After more than five years of investigation and consultation the university began at the end of 2010.<ref>[http://www.aau.org/ Association of African Universities (AAU)]</ref>\n\n== Campus ==\nBaresan University has one campus in [[Banaadir]]\n\n=== Mogadishu campus ===\nThe main campus is located in [[Mogadishu]] [[Banaadir|Banadir]].\n\n== Academics ==\nThe [[university]] offers [[Undergraduate education|undergraduate]] courses in the [[natural science]]s, the [[social science]]s, the [[Technology]] and professional [[Higher education|studies]]. [[Scholarship]]s are available.\n\nThe medium of instruction in [[Undergraduate education|undergraduate]] programs is [[English language|English]] and [[Arabic]]. Applicants are required to pass an [[English language|English]] [[Test (assessment)|examination]] if they are from a non-English speaking country. [[English language|Engalish]] language support at all levels is provided by the Languages Unit.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://baresanuniversity.net/colleges/ |title=Baresan University Colleges |access-date=2016-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416002127/http://baresanuniversity.net/colleges/ |archive-date=2016-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Colleges ==\n=== Economics and Management Science College ===\n* Faculty of [[Business management|Business Management]]\n* Faculty of [[Banking and Finance|Banking & Finance]]\n* Faculty of [[Accounting]]\n* Faculty of [[Economics]]\n* Faculty of [[Marketing]]\n* Faculty of [[Human resource management|HRM]]\n\n=== Agriculture and Vet medicine College ===\n* Faculty of [[Agriculture]]\n* Faculty of [[Veterinary medicine|Veterinary Medicine]]\n\n=== Medicine & Health Science College ===\n* Faculty of [[Medicine|Medicine & Surgery]]\n* Faculty of [[Medical laboratory|Medical Laboratory]]\n* Faculty of [[Public health|Public Health]]\n* Faculty Of [[Neuroscience]]\n* Faculty Of [[Nutrition]]\n\n=== Education & Mass Media College ===\n* Faculty of [[Education]]\n* Faculty of [[Journalism]]\n\n=== Engineering College ===\n* Faculty of [[Computer science|Computer Science]]\n* Faculty of [[Civil engineering|Civil Engineering]]\n\n=== Islamic Studies College ===\n* Faculty of [[Sharia|Sharia & Law]]\n\n=== Languages College ===\n* Faculty of [[Arabic|Arabic Language]]\n* Faculty of [[English literature|English Literature]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Somalia}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160415221818/http://baresanuniversity.net/ Official website]\n\n{{coord missing|Somalia}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Baresan, Baresan University}}\n[[Category:Universities in Somalia]]\n[[Category:Mogadishu]]\n[[Category:Lower Shabelle]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2010]]\n[[Category:2010 establishments in Somalia]]\n", "text_old": "{{more citations needed|date=April 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n| name = Baresan University\n| caption = \u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629 \u0628\u0631\u064a\u0633\u0646\n| motto = Education is a powerful Weapon to change the World.\n| established = 2010\n| type = [[Private university|Private]]\n| rector = Dr. [[Abdi Abdullahi Mohamed]]\n| president = Dr [[Abdulrazak Adam Jimale]]\n| students = 2,625\n| undergrad = 2,195\n| postgrad = 430\n| city = [[Mogadishu]]\n| state = [[Banaadir]]\n| country = [[Somalia]]\n| campus = [[Mogadishu|Mogadishu Campus]], [[Lower Shabelle|Lower Shabelle Compus]]\n| nickname = BSU\n| website = {{url|http://baresanuniversity.net/}}\n| logo = \n| image_name = \n| colors = Orange and Navy<br />{{color box|#f29320}}&nbsp;{{color box|#303083}}\n}}\n\n'''Baresan University''' ('''BSU''') ([[Arabic language|Arabic]]: \u062c\u0627\u0645\u0639\u0629 \u0628\u0631\u064a\u0633\u0646, [[Somali language|Somali]]: ''Jaamacada Bare san'') is a [[Private university|private]] [[higher education]] [[institution]] which is [[non-political]], [[Nonpartisanism|non-partisan]] and [[Nonsectarian|non-sectarian]]. It was established in 2010. Baresan University was established at a time when young Somali [[Secondary school|secondary]] graduates could hardly get an opportunity to continue their [[education]] after [[secondary school]] due to the scarcity of tertiary [[education]] [[institution]]s in [[Somalia]].\n\n== History ==\nThe collapse of the [[Somalia|Somali state]] and the subsequent [[Somali Civil War|civil war]](s) from 1990s have altered most aspects of [[Somali people|Somali]] lives ; but they have been particularly devastating in the area of [[education]], where an entire [[generation]] has lost out on one of the most precious opportunities of [[childhood]] and adults. The restoration of regular schooling and [[Somalia universities|universities]] are critical if [[Somali people|Somalis]] expect to survive the present upheaval and envision a hopeful [[future]].\n\nThe scheme to launch Baresan University was advanced by a group of intellectuals led by Dr [[Abdulrazak Adam Jimale]]. After more than five years of investigation and consultation the university began at the end of 2010.<ref>[http://www.aau.org/ Association of African Universities (AAU)]</ref>\n\n== Campus ==\nBaresan University has one campus in [[Banaadir]]\n\n=== Mogadishu campus ===\nThe main campus is located in [[Mogadishu]] [[Banaadir|Banadir]].\n\n== Academics ==\nThe [[university]] offers [[Undergraduate education|undergraduate]] courses in the [[natural science]]s, the [[social science]]s, the [[Technology]] and professional [[Higher education|studies]]. [[Scholarship]]s are available.\n\nThe medium of instruction in [[Undergraduate education|undergraduate]] programs is [[English language|English]] and [[Arabic]]. Applicants are required to pass an [[English language|English]] [[Test (assessment)|examination]] if they are from a non-English speaking country. [[English language|Engalish]] language support at all levels is provided by the Languages Unit.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://baresanuniversity.net/colleges/ |title=Baresan University Colleges |access-date=2016-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160416002127/http://baresanuniversity.net/colleges/ |archive-date=2016-04-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n== Colleges ==\n=== Economics and Management Science College ===\n* Faculty of [[Business management|Business Management]]\n* Faculty of [[Banking and Finance|Banking & Finance]]\n* Faculty of [[Accounting]]\n* Faculty of [[Economics]]\n* Faculty of [[Marketing]]\n* Faculty of [[Human resource management|HRM]]\n\n=== Agriculture and Vet medicine College ===\n* Faculty of [[Agriculture]]\n* Faculty of [[Veterinary medicine|Veterinary Medicine]]\n\n=== Medicine & Health Science College ===\n* Faculty of [[Medicine|Medicine & Surgery]]\n* Faculty of [[Medical laboratory|Medical Laboratory]]\n* Faculty of [[Public health|Public Health]]\n* Faculty Of [[Neuroscience]]\n* Faculty Of [[Nutrition]]\n\n=== Education & Mass Media College ===\n* Faculty of [[Education]]\n* Faculty of [[Journalism]]\n\n=== Engineering College ===\n* Faculty of [[Computer science|Computer Science]]\n* Faculty of [[Civil engineering|Civil Engineering]]\n\n=== Islamic Studies College ===\n* Faculty of [[Sharia|Sharia & Law]]\n\n=== Languages College ===\n* Faculty of [[Arabic|Arabic Language]]\n* Faculty of [[English literature|English Literature]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Portal|Somalia}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160415221818/http://baresanuniversity.net/ Official website]\n\n{{coord missing|Somalia}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Baresan, Baresan University}}\n[[Category:Universities in Somalia]]\n[[Category:Mogadishu]]\n[[Category:Lower Shabelle]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2010]]\n[[Category:2010 establishments in Somalia]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baresan_University"}
{"title_page": "Barcelona School of Agricultural Engineering", "text_new": "{{multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=April 2015}}\n{{unreferenced|date=April 2015}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n|native_name            = Escola Superior d'Agricultura de Barcelona \n|name      = Barcelona School of Agricultural Engineering\n|image_name      =  \n|caption         = \n|established     = 1911\n|type       = Public \n|endowment       =  \n|director        = Lourdes Reig Puig\n|city            = [[Castelldefels]]\n|state = [[Catalonia]]\n|country = [[Spain]]\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.esab.upc.edu/}}}}\n\nThe '''Barcelona School of Agricultural Engineering''' (Escola Superior d'Agricultura de Barcelona - ESAB) is a university center founded in 1912. ESAB is nowadays an engineering school of the [[Polytechnic University of Catalonia|UPC-BarcelonaTech]] offering bachelor's and master's degrees in the field of [[Biosystems engineering]].\n\nIn 1911 the President of the Provincial Council of Barcelona, the great patrician [[Enric Prat de la Riba]], promoted the creation of the College of Agriculture of Barcelona and on July 11 of that year approved the corresponding order. On October 25, the first board of the school was established and Mr. Manuel Raventos and Domenech was designed as first director of the School. The ESAB settled into a new factory building at Can Batllo (now the site of the Industrial School of Barcelona) which has 10 hectares of experimental fields in the land around him. 1912-1913 was the first academic year with seven students admitted.\n\nThe school had a dual purpose: firstly, to train farmers in a good scientific practice. Secondly, to become a research center helping to solve the problems faced by the national agriculture.\n\nCurrently, ESAB organize and participates in several bachelor's and master's degrees.\n\nBachelor's degrees:\n\n'''Agricultural Engineering.'''\nModern agriculture, efficient and technologically advanced based on respect for the environment and animal welfare .\n\n'''Agricultural Environmental and Landscape Engineering.'''\nLandscape and environmental management of natural resources and green spaces for a better world.\n\n'''Food Engineering.'''\nFood industry, food and beverage processing, control and food safety, probiotics, foods high value, ...\n\n'''Biosystems Engineering.'''\nBiotechnology applied to food and bioprocesses industry, waste management and environment.\n\n'''Culinary and Gastronomic Sciences.'''\nScience and technology applied to good food.\n\nMaster's degrees:\n\n'''KET 4 Food + Bio.'''\nEnabling technologies (robotics, nanotechnology, photonics, ...) applied to the food and bioprocesses industry.\n\n'''Aquaculture.'''\nAquaculture techniques studied from multidisciplinary management and management of associated industries.\n\n'''Plant Breeding.'''\nDevelopment of new varieties with hybridization and selection methods and new biotechnologies.\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.esab.upc.edu P\u00e0gina web oficial]\n\n{{coord|41.2758|N|1.9864|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Schools in Barcelona]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Spain]]\n", "text_old": "{{multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=April 2015}}\n{{unreferenced|date=April 2015}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox university\n|native_name            = Escola Superior d'Agricultura de Barcelona \n|name      = Barcelona School of Agricultural Engineering\n|image_name      =  \n|caption         = \n|established     = 1911\n|type       = Public \n|endowment       =  \n|director        = Lourdes Reig Puig\n|city            = [[Castelldefels]]\n|state = [[Catalonia]]\n|country = [[Spain]]\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.esab.upc.edu/}}}}\n\nThe '''Barcelona School of Agricultural Engineering''' (Escola Superior d'Agricultura de Barcelona - ESAB) is a university center founded in 1912. ESAB is nowadays an engineering school of the [[Polytechnic University of Catalonia|UPC-BarcelonaTech]] offering bachelor's and master's degrees in the field of [[Biosystems engineering]].\n\nIn 1911 the President of the Provincial Council of Barcelona, the great patrician [[Enric Prat de la Riba]], promoted the creation of the College of Agriculture of Barcelona and on July 11 of that year approved the corresponding order. On October 25, the first board of the school was established and Mr. Manuel Raventos and Domenech was designed as first director of the School. The ESAB settled into a new factory building at Can Batllo (now the site of the Industrial School of Barcelona) which has 10 hectares of experimental fields in the land around him. 1912-1913 was the first academic year with seven students admitted.\n\nThe school had a dual purpose: firstly, to train farmers in a good scientific practice. Secondly, to become a research center helping to solve the problems faced by the national agriculture.\n\nCurrently, ESAB organize and participates in several bachelor's and master's degrees.\n\nBachelor's degrees:\n\n'''Agricultural Engineering.'''\nModern agriculture, efficient and technologically advanced based on respect for the environment and animal welfare .\n\n'''Agricultural Environmental and Landscape Engineering.'''\nLandscape and environmental management of natural resources and green spaces for a better world.\n\n'''Food Engineering.'''\nFood industry, food and beverage processing, control and food safety, probiotics, foods high value, ...\n\n'''Biosystems Engineering.'''\nBiotechnology applied to food and bioprocesses industry, waste management and environment.\n\n'''Culinary and Gastronomic Sciences.'''\nScience and technology applied to good food.\n\nMaster's degrees:\n\n'''KET 4 Food + Bio.'''\nEnabling technologies (robotics, nanotechnology, photonics, ...) applied to the food and bioprocesses industry.\n\n'''Aquaculture.'''\nAquaculture techniques studied from multidisciplinary management and management of associated industries.\n\n'''Plant Breeding.'''\nDevelopment of new varieties with hybridization and selection methods and new biotechnologies.\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.esab.upc.edu P\u00e0gina web oficial]\n\n{{coord|41.2758|N|1.9864|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Schools in Barcelona]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Spain]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barcelona_School_of_Agricultural_Engineering"}
